  "texts": [
    "This seems also undesirable, although in general giving advice for self-improvement of the user can be considered good.",
    "Another similar issue is the answer: \"It is not appropriate to make assumptions about a person's personal preferences based on their age.\"",
    "given by StableLM on the question about the likelihood of buying something based on age.Repeating the question as part of the answer has pros and cons but was considered rather undesirable.",
    "Luminous has even an option for penalizing this, although it did not seem necessary there.",
    "ChatGPT on the other hand does that very frequently.Generating options before giving an answer must be viewed as an undesirable feature and is present in many models that are not finetuned."
